2009-03-27  Hubert Degaudenzi  <Hubert.Degaudenzi@cern.ch>

	* python/LbConfiguration/LbLogin.py: rewritten completely the Site massaging
	part:
	   - the MYSITEROOT value has full priority over any other setting. It cannot
	   be passed to the script through the environment. It has to be explicitly passed
	   as argument.
	   - if no MYSITEROOT value is available, the CMTSITE value is used. This one can be
	   read from the environment and it can have 3 possible values LOCAL, CERN, standalone.
	      * the LOCAL value is trying to guess the MYSITEROOT value
	      * the CERN value is trying to local the /afs/cern.ch directory
	      * the standalone value is setting nothing and is used for the building of the project.
	   If any of these attempt is failing, it falls back on the next one.
	   - if neither MYSITEROOT nor CMTSITE is available, the 3 possibilities are tried
	   - if everything fails, the standalone mode is chosen.

